raw_data.title: Technical Project Manager
raw_data.description: Responsible for providing overall management of the contractor team including delegation of work assignments; submitting monthly invoices, progress reports, and issue logs; developing work plans and budgets; ensuring all work is professional, error-free, and completed within established timelines and budgets; participate as requested in meeting and conferences; develop program and training content in alignment with Federal policy and guidance; acting as the primary point of contact between the Contractor team and Federal; quickly resolving work or personnel  related issues to the satisfaction of Federal; guiding or assisting with any task defined in the Statement of Work; other program management responsibilities to ensure successful execution of all work assignments.

raw_data.title: Lead Reviewer
raw_data.description: Responsible for leading Comprehensive Oversight/Compliance Review, Special Assignment, Technical Assistance, and Corrective Action Support tasks; authoring reports and technical memoranda; reviewing deliverables for assigned tasks to ensure completion and accuracy; developing program and training content in alignment with Federal policy and guidance; participate in conference calls, meetings, and conferences as needed; attending and provide expertise during grantee workshops; and other responsibilities to ensure successful execution of all work assignments.

raw_data.title: Associate Reviewer
raw_data.description: Responsible for assisting with Comprehensive Oversight/Compliance Reviews; leading or assisting with Special Assignment, Technical Assistance, and Corrective Action Support tasks; drafting reports and technical memoranda; assisting with the development of program and training content in alignment with Federal policy and guidance; participating in conference calls, meetings, and conferences as needed; attend and provide expertise during grantee workshops; and other responsibilities to ensure successful execution of all work assignments.

raw_data.title: Lead Trainer/Facilitator
raw_data.description: Responsible for facilitating grantee workshops, webinars, oversight events, and other Program Oversight-related meetings; lead compliance training sessions (including workshops) for single or multiple Federal recipients.

raw_data.title: Lead Event Planner
raw_data.description: Responsible for planning and execution of Program Oversight events including grantee workshops, annual meetings, and other events.

raw_data.title: Workshop Registrar
raw_data.description: Responsible for assisting with the planning and execution of Program Oversight events including grantee workshops, annual meetings, and other events.

raw_data.title: Audit Partner
raw_data.description: Oversees all aspects of an organization's auditing function. Responsible for planning and directing all accounting and financial data.  Subject matter expertise in a variety of accounting and auditing guidelines concepts, practices, and procedures. Relies on extensive experience and judgment to plan and accomplish goals. Performs a variety of tasks. Leads and directs the work of others. Serves as engagement partner on client engagements with the authority to commit firm resources. Responsible for developing new audit-related business opportunities. Job functions require exercising independent judgment and creativity.

raw_data.title: Audit Manager/Project Lead
raw_data.description: Directs a group of auditors for various, complex auditing projects. Identifies improper accounting or documentation and researches issues and makes recommendations to improve policies or procedures accordingly. Works with outside auditors to help reconcile discrepancies or support the external auditing function

raw_data.title: Staff Auditor
raw_data.description: Audits the accounting and financial data of various departments within an organization to ensure accuracy and compliance with government guidelines and laws. Identifies improper accounting or documentation and researches issues and makes recommendations to improve policies or procedures accordingly. Work with outside auditors to help reconcile discrepancies or support the external auditing function. Familiarity with standard accounting and auditing guidelines, concepts, practices, and procedures. Relies on limited experience and judgment to plan and accomplish goals. Performs a variety of tasks. Works under general supervision and typically reports to an audit project lead or manager. Job functions require exercising some independent judgment.
